From 64cdcc7b45c0cb4e4cad07a56d631b32e35326cd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Fabio M. Di Nitto" <fdinitto@redhat.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 10:34:01 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Fix wall-powered outlet power-up failure

Problem: Wall-powered outlets (keys 1 and 2 in anvil-tnf setup) could be
powered down via CLI but failed to power back up. The power-up command
would silently fail, leaving the outlet in off state even with wall
voltage available.

Root Cause: The `_set_parent_oid_states()` method in outlet.py was
attempting to call `Redis.mset()` with an empty dictionary when the outlet
had no parent OIDs. Wall-powered outlets don't have SNMP interfaces, so
`GraphReference.get_parent_keys()` returns an empty OID dict. Redis
rejects mset() with empty arguments, throwing "wrong number of arguments
for 'mset' command", which prevented power_up() from completing.

Solution: Added a check in `_set_parent_oid_states()` to return early if
there are no parent OIDs. This allows wall-powered outlets to skip SNMP
synchronization (which they don't need) and proceed with normal power-up
logic.

Impact: Wall-powered outlets can now be power-cycled via CLI commands.
PDU/UPS-connected outlets with SNMP continue to work as before (commit
680b8e5 already fixed their SNMP sync).

Files Changed:
- enginecore/state/api/outlet.py: Added empty OID check in
  _set_parent_oid_states()

Tested: Full power cycle of wall outlet (down/up/down/up) works correctly
on anvil-ci-bm-phy01 test cluster.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 enginecore/enginecore/state/api/outlet.py | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/enginecore/enginecore/state/api/outlet.py b/enginecore/enginecore/state/api/outlet.py
index debc328..8ed7adb 100644
--- a/enginecore/enginecore/state/api/outlet.py
+++ b/enginecore/enginecore/state/api/outlet.py
@@ -26,6 +26,10 @@ class IOutletStateManager(ISnmpDeviceStateManager):
         with graph_ref.get_session() as session:
             _, oids = GraphReference.get_parent_keys(session, self.key)
 
+        # Skip if no parent OIDs (wall-powered outlets don't have SNMP)
+        if not oids:
+            return
+
         oid_keys = oids.keys()
         parents_new_states = {}
         parent_values = self.get_store().mget(oid_keys)
-- 
